<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style>
      h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p {
      margin-bottom: 10px; }
    </mj-style>
    <!-- <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto+Serif" /> -->
    <mj-font
      name="Roboto+Serif"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?faily=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap"
    />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff" padding-bottom="0px">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image
          padding="10px 12px"
          css-class="light_img"
          width="140px"
          src="https://www.dubaisummary.com/logo-grey.png"
          href="https://www.dubaisummary.com"
          alt=""
        />
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 0px"
        />
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 2px 0px 2px"
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          color="#000000"
        >
        </mj-text>
        <!-- weather image -->
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 0px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.dubaisummary.com/email/images/dubai-weather-july-15.jpg"
          alt="Dubai weather july 15"
          href="https://www.dubaisummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 2px 0px 2px"
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>In this edition:</strong>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-table
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          cellpadding="0"
          cellspacing="0"
          padding="10px 18px 10px 18px"
          style="width: 100%"
        >
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6">
              Firms fined for breaking tax rules
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; line-height: 1.6">
              Shreya Ghoshal live concert
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td
              style="
                font-size: 18px;
                width: 20px;
                vertical-align: top;
                padding-right: 8px;
                line-height: 1.6;
              "
            >
              →
            </td>
            <td style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; line-height: 1.6">
              How Dubai saved Live Aid in 1985
            </td>
          </tr>
        </mj-table>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Header -->
    <!-- breaking news-->
    <!-- /breaking news -->
    <mj-spacer height="10px" />
    <!-- Spotlight -->
    <mj-section
      css-class="mj_fsection"
      background-color="#ffffff"
      css-class="mj_fsection"
    >
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text
          padding="2px 12px 0px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="white"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              padding-top: 14px;
              padding-bottom: 8px;
              color: #102341;
              text-align: left;
              border-bottom: 2px solid #102341;

              font-size: 26px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
            "
          >
            Spotlight
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff" padding-bottom="6px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            Law for contractors
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.dubaisummary.com/email/images/contracting-activities-regulation-development-committee-key-feature.jpg"
          alt="A key feature is the creation of the Contracting Activities Regulation and Development Committee"
          href="https://www.dubaisummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              A key feature is the creation of the Contracting Activities
              Regulation and Development Committee. Credits: Gulf News
            </i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px 16px 12px"
          font-family="Roboto+Serif"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Dubai Ruler, Sheikh Mohammed, has issued a
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #102341;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-law-to-regulate?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >law to regulate</a
            >
            all contracting and construction companies in Dubai. The goal is to
            ensure every contractor follows the same rules, has the right
            qualifications, and operates within approved limits. The law also
            bans subcontracting without permission.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            A committee will oversee the system, and Dubai Municipality will set
            up a central electronic registry of all contractors. The law applies
            to all companies in Dubai and its open trade zones, except for some
            major infrastructure projects, like airports. Contractors who
            violate the rules could face hefty fines, suspension, or even have
            their license revoked.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            This update follows Dubai’s broader reforms to raise construction
            standards, with an
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #102341;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-15-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-evaluation-system?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >evaluation system</a
            >
            coming in 2026. Two engineering firms have already been suspended
            for violations.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider
          border-width="1px"
          border-style="solid"
          border-color="lightgrey"
          padding="10px 12px 0px 12px"
        />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-text
          padding="10px 12px"
          font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;"
          color="#000000"
        >
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            "
          >
            Tax fines for UAE firms
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image
          border-radius="10px"
          padding="10px 12px"
          width="600px"
          src="https://www.dubaisummary.com/email/images/sca-importance-of-regulatory-compliance.jpg"
          alt="The SCA emphasised the importance of following the rules of all relevant international and domestic regulators"
          href="https://www.dubaisummary.com"
        />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>
              The SCA emphasized the importance of following the rules of all
              relevant international and domestic regulators. Credits: Khaleej
              Times</i
            >
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The UAE has fined several
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #102341;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-15-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-licensed-monetary-companies?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >licensed monetary companies</a
            >
            a total of Dh325,000 for failing to comply with international tax
            rules, including the Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act (FATCA) and
            the Common Reporting Standard (CRS). These regulations aim to
            prevent tax evasion and increase monetary transparency worldwide.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            The Securities and Commodities Authority (SCA) found reporting and
            compliance issues during investigations and urged all firms to
            strengthen their internal systems.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter: blur(5px)">
            This is part of a broader push in 2025 to align the UAE’s monetary
            system with international standards and protect the integrity of its
            markets. As a sign of its progress, the European Commission recently
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #102341;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.dubaisummary.com/ds-15-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-removed-the-uae?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >removed the UAE</a
            >
            from its list of “high-risk third countries” for currency laundering
            and terrorist financing.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>
